    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>10th Standard Maths Assignment</title>
    



    <h1>10th Standard Maths Assignment</h1>

    <h2>Date: 24-12-2025</h2>
    <div class="question-container">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Geometry]</span> 
                Draw tangents to a circle of radius 5 cm from a point 10 cm away from the center. Also, calculate the lengths of the tangents.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Statistics]</span> 
                The wages of 10 employees are given below. Find the variance and standard deviation of the wages.<br>
                <strong>Data:</strong> Ōé╣310, Ōé╣290, Ōé╣320, Ōé╣280, Ōé╣300, Ōé╣290, Ōé╣320, Ōé╣310, Ōé╣280.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Matrices]</span> 
                If <span class="matrix">A = [[1, 2], [1, 3]]</span>, <span class="matrix">B = [[4, 0], [1, 5]]</span>, <span class="matrix">C = [[2, 0], [1, 2]]</span>, verify that <i>(A - B)C = AC - BC</i>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Algebra]</span> 
                Find the square root of the following polynomial by division method:<br>
                121x<sup>4</sup> - 198x<sup>3</sup> - 183x<sup>2</sup> + 216x + 144
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h2>Date: 26-12-2025</h2>
    <div class="question-container">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Geometry]</span> 
                Construct a triangle similar to a given triangle PQR with its sides equal to 2/3 of the corresponding sides of the triangle PQR (Scale factor 2/3).
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Statistics]</span> 
                Find the coefficient of variation for the following data: 24, 26, 33, 37, 29, 31.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Matrices]</span> 
                If <span class="matrix">A = [[5, 2, 9], [1, 2, 8]]</span> and <span class="matrix">B = [[1, 7], [1, 2], [5, -1]]</span>, verify that <i>(AB)<sup>T</sup> = B<sup>T</sup>A<sup>T</sup></i>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Algebra]</span> 
                Find the square root of the following polynomial by division method:<br>
                x<sup>4</sup> - 12x<sup>3</sup> + 42x<sup>2</sup> - 36x + 9
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h2>Date: 27-12-2025</h2>
    <div class="question-container">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Geometry]</span> 
                Draw a circle of diameter 6 cm and mark a point 5 cm away from the center. Draw tangents from that point to the circle and calculate the lengths of the tangents.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Probability]</span> 
                Three fair coins are tossed simultaneously. Find the probability of getting:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>All heads</li>
                    <li>At least one tail</li>
                    <li>At most one head</li>
                    <li>At most two tails</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Matrices]</span> 
                If <span class="matrix">A = [[3, 1], [-1, 2]]</span>, prove that <i>A<sup>2</sup> - 5A + 7I = 0</i>.
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Algebra]</span> 
                Find the square root of the following polynomial by division method: 6x<sup>4</sup> + 8x<sup>2</sup> + 1.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h2>Date: 29-12-2025</h2>
    <div class="question-container">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Geometry]</span> 
                Construct a triangle similar to a given triangle PQR with its sides equal to 7/4 of the corresponding sides of the triangle PQR (Scale factor 7/4 &gt; 1).
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Probability]</span> 
                A bag contains 5 red balls, 6 white balls, 7 green balls, and 8 black balls. One ball is drawn at random. Find the probability that the ball is:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>White</li>
                    <li>Black or Red</li>
                    <li>Not White</li>
                    <li>Neither White nor Black</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Algebra]</span> 
                If the following are perfect square polynomials, find the values of 'a' and 'b':
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>4x<sup>4</sup> - 12x<sup>3</sup> + 37x<sup>2</sup> + bx + a</li>
                    <li>ax<sup>4</sup> + bx<sup>3</sup> + 361x<sup>2</sup> + 220x + 100</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Matrices]</span> 
                Solve for x and y: <span class="matrix">[[x<sup>2</sup>], [y<sup>2</sup>]] + 2[[-2x], [-y]] = [[-5], [8]]</span>.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h2>Date: 30-12-2025</h2>
    <div class="question-container">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Coordinate Geometry]</span> 
                Find the area of the quadrilateral formed by the given points:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>(-9, -2), (-8, 4), (2, 2), (1, -3)</li>
                    <li>(-9, 0), (-8, 6), (-1, -2), (-6, -3)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Graph]</span> 
                Draw the graph of <i>xy = 24, x,y &gt; 0</i>. Using the graph:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>Find y when x = 3.</li>
                    <li>Find x when y = 6.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Probability]</span> 
                A bag contains 6 green balls and some black and red balls. The number of black balls is twice the number of red balls. The probability of getting a green ball is three times the probability of getting a red ball. Find:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>The number of black balls.</li>
                    <li>The total number of balls.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Functions]</span> 
                A function f:[-5,9] ŌåÆ R is defined as follows:<br>
                f(x) = { 6x + 1 if -5 Ōēż x &lt; 2; <br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5x<sup>2</sup> - 1 if 2 Ōēż x &lt; 6; <br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3x - 4 if 6 Ōēż x Ōēż 9 }<br>
                Find:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>f(-3) + f(2)</li>
                    <li>f(7) - f(1)</li>
                    <li>2f(4) + f(8)</li>
                    <li>(2f(-2) - f(6)) / (f(4) + f(-2))</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h2>Date: 31-12-2025 (Set 1)</h2>
    <div class="question-container">
        <ol>
            <li>
                <span class="category">[Sets]</span> 
                Given A = {x Ōłł N | 1 &lt; x &lt; 4}, B = {x Ōłł W | 0 Ōēż x &lt; 2}, C = {x Ōłł N | x &lt; 3}. Verify:
                <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>A x (B U C) = (A x B) U (A x C)</li>
                    <li>A x (B Ōł® C) = (A x B) Ōł® (A x C)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
